&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;sigma; and &amp;pi; Bonds in Chemical Structures&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;sigma; (sigma) bonds are single covalent bonds formed by the head-on overlapping of atomic orbitals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;pi; (pi) bonds are additional bonds formed by the side-on overlapping of p orbitals, typically found in double and triple bonds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EXPLANATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;title&gt;&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONCEPT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonds in Various Molecules&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
